This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Barack Obama on April 29, 2016. The memorandum is titled "Promoting Rehabilitation and Reintegration of Formerly Incarcerated Individuals" and emphasizes the importance of providing second chances to individuals who have completed their sentences. The memorandum aims to promote the rehabilitation and reintegration of formerly incarcerated individuals in order to make communities safer, reduce recidivism, and save taxpayer dollars. It establishes the Federal Interagency Reentry Council, which includes various government departments and agencies, to coordinate efforts in achieving these goals. The memorandum also addresses the need to reduce barriers to employment for individuals with criminal records and encourages agencies to review their procedures for evaluating applicants' criminal records. It concludes with general provisions and authorizes the Attorney General to publish the memorandum in the Federal Register.